 Requirements:

 Introduction:
A contact management is a software program that enables users to easily store and find contact information, such as names, addresses, and telephone numbers. They are contact-centric databases that provide a fully integrated approach to tracking all information and communication activities linked to contacts.

Research:
Contact management is the act of storing, organizing , and tracking information about your customers, prospects, and sales leads CRM tools typically provide contact management functionality but add features that help businesses manage their relationships.

SWOT analysis:

Strengths
.We can easily store information
.search contacts
.delete contacts
.contact management increases customer satisfaction

Opportunities
.sync all your accounts
.can be used for marketing,sales etc
.Automation of process

Weakness
.Keep data up to date
.Better user interface	

Threats
.security
.storage issues




HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS:
